{
  "text": "The theoretical background of this numerical exploration was the following. By backward error analysis (see [CITATION_1] Ch. IX] ) it can be shown that applying a symplectic integrator to an integrable Hamiltonian systems gives a symplectic map x j → x j+1 and also (#) small error in energy uniformly for long time, error growth linear in t for exponentially long times (see [CITATION_2] Ch. X] ). Behaviour (#) can also be shown for symmetric time integrators when applied to integrable Hamiltonian systems (see [CITATION_3] Ch. XI] ).",
  "correct_citation": {
